review: Super professional, incredibly ************* and most of all the first gynae who did not treat me as a 20-something first time pregnant newly married girl, and which I most certainly was not. I am a working professional in my 30s and very much capable of discussing and understanding challenges with pregnancy, risks etc. I really wanted to meet someone who would treat me professionally and with whom I could discuss everything that was bothering me. And Dr. Aneja is amazing at that! Thank you so much for professionally guiding me all throughout.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review: She is an Amazing doctor and helping me survive through the toughest pregnancy. Carrying twins with so many complications wasn’t easy but she  gave me the hope and made me stay positive throughout. I am grateful to the hands that helped bring my babies into this world.
